Check Installed R and Python Dependencies for MOSAIC

Source: R/check_dependencies.R
check_dependencies.Rd

This function checks the MOSAIC Python conda environment, verifies that the expected Python packages are installed, and confirms that the R packages keras3 and tensorflow are present and configured correctly. It prints the currently active Python configuration and confirms whether the backend is working.

Usage

check_dependencies()

Value

No return value. Prints diagnostic messages about environment status and package versions.
